<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="803" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d803">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that a constitutional government will be proclaimed
                            to-night; full parliamentary government, the Emperor reserving <pb facs="0897" n="777" xml:id="pg_777"/> the right of veto; freedom of
                            the press and person and of speech, habeas corpus, and inviolability of
                            domicile. The parliament appoints the ministers. The franchise is
                            extended to all classes. Count Witte, prime minister.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>